@node Configuring
@next Troubleshooting
@prev Usage
PR-QWK is configured entirely by @{"UMS config variables." link UMSConfigVariables}

The variables are:

qwk.arcCmd:
   The command to add a file to an archive. Put %d in inplace of the name
   of the archive, and %s inplace of the name of the file.

   Default: "lha a %d %s"

qwk.bufferSize
   The size, in bytes, of the buffer used when reading from or writing to
   files. If the program cannot allocate that much memory, it will
   try 4k, then give up.

   Default: "16384" (16k)

qwk.dearcCmd:
   The command to extract files from an archive. Put %s in inplace of the
   name of the archive.

   Default: "lha x %s"

qwk.inbound:
   The name of the directory where QWK packets are found.

   Default: "DOWNLOADS:"

qwk.MailFolder
   The name of the folder to put an mailed files (more about that later) in.

   Default: ""

qwk.outbound:
   The name of the directory to put reply packets.

   Default: "UPLOADS:"

qwk.site
   The ID of the BBS where you got the QWK packet from. If you are
unsure, the name of the QWK packet will be this name with .QWK on the end.

   Default: "QWK"

qwk.tempdir
   The name of the directory used to store files that are being worked on.
Make sure there are no files you want to keep in that directory, because
the entire contents is deleted by PR-QWK.

   Default: "T:"

qwk.MailBulletins, qwk.MailGoodBye, qwk.MailNew, qwk.MailNewFiles,
qwk.MailSession, qwk.MailWelcome:
   These are variables used to tell PR-QWK which, if any, of files
that may be included in the QWK packet should be mailed to the user
that the packet belongs to.

   Default: qwk.MailNews and qwk.MailNewFiles default to TRUE,
            the rest default to FALSE.

qwk.ShowBulletins, qwk.ShowGoodBye, qwk.ShowNew, qwk.ShowNewFiles,
qwk.ShowSession, qwk.ShowWelcome:
   These are variables used to tell PR-QWK which, if any, of files
that may be included in the QWK packet should be displayed.

   Default: qwk.ShowWelcome and qwk.ShowGoodbye default to TRUE,
            the rest default to FALSE.
@endnode

