@node Installation
@next Usage
@prev Features
Just copy UMSQWK to wherever you keep your UMS binaries, this documentation
to wherever you keep UMS documenation and the configure it (see
Configuration).
@endnode

@node Introduction
@next Features
@prev Main
PR QWK is a QWK importer and exporter for UMS. Unlike most UMS importers
and exporters, the same program does both importing and exporting.

You will, of course, need a copy of UMS 11.6 or higher.
@endnode

@node TestResults
Tests were done on an Amiga 1200, with 6mb of RAM, and a 540MB IDE HD.
Temporary dir was on HD.
MB was cleaned before all tests.
Timings are accurate to 0.5 seconds.

Importing:

  3 tests were done, once on each of three packets. Each packet came from
  a different BBS.

  PR-QWK:  140 messages, taking 10 seconds to import. 14 messages/second
  UMS-QWK: 140 messages, taking 12 seconds to import. 12 messages/second

  PR-QWK:  113 messages, taking 6 seconds to import. 18 messages/second
  UMS-QWK: 113 messages, taking 10 seconds to import. 11 messages/second

  PR-QWK:  26 messages, taking 1 second to import. 26 messages/second
  UMS-QWK: Crashed

Exporting:
  Results for exporting are currently unavailable.
@endnode

@node Troubleshooting
@next Bugs
@prev Configuring
Problem:
   "Error allocating -127 bytes for message buffer.
    Reason: Insufficient free memory for allocation."

Reason:
   The packet if incorrect. I can't remember the exact problem, but it
   results in PR-QWK trying to read in a message that isn't there.

   Either get your packets from somewhere else, or don't worry about it.

   Oh, and it says insufficient free memory because when allocating it
   thinks of negative numbers as something above 2,147,483,648 bytes.
@endnode

@node UMSConfigVariables
These are variables stored in the UMS config, and can be read by programs
using UMS.

To edit them, either use a text editor to edit the config file by hand,
or use a GUI UMS config editor, such as ConfUMS.
@endnode

@node Usage
@next Configuring
@prev Installation
PRQWK NAME/K,PASSWORD=PWD/K,SERVER=SRV/K,NOEXPORT/S,NOIMPORT/S,KEEP/S,
      DEBUG/S

NAME     is the user name to login in as. Defaults to "qwk.default".

PASSWORD is the password for that user. Defaults to "".

SERVER   is the name of the server to login in to. Defaults to "default".

NOEXPORT tells PR-QWK to not export.

NOIMPORT tells PR-QWK to not import.

KEEP     tells PR-QWK to not delete a QWK packet after importing it.

DEBUG    tells PR-QWK to print out additional error messages.
@endnode
